# Udinsk, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Udinsk (; , Khakhirai Ürtöö) is a rural locality (a selo) in Khorinsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 719 as of 2010. There are 10 streets.
Geography
Udinsk is located 43&nbsp;km west of Khorinsk (the district's administrative centre) by road. Tarbagatay is the nearest rural locality.
